**Workflow:**
User -> Planner;
Planner -> WebSearcher (search 'Yola gimlie');
WebSearcher -> WebBrowser (open wiktionary link);
WebBrowser -> Planner (extract Latin root 'caminata');
Planner -> WebSearcher (search 'Collins Spanish-to-English dictionary caminata');
WebSearcher -> WebBrowser (open Collins URL);
WebBrowser -> Planner (extract 1994 example source title);
Planner -> WebSearcher (search translation of source title);
WebSearcher -> Summarizer;
Summarizer -> End.

**Description:**
First, the Planner analyzes the query and creates a step-by-step plan. The WebSearcher identifies the Latin root 'caminata' via a search, and the WebBrowser navigates to Wiktionary to confirm it. Next, the WebSearcher locates the Collins dictionary entry for 'caminata', and the WebBrowser extracts the 1994 example's source title. Finally, the WebSearcher retrieves the Google translation of the title, and the Summarizer combines all findings into the final answer.
